Topic:11 user management in Linux:
----------------------------------
.Manage users and groups using command-line tools
.Create, modify, view and delete users and groups
.groups nothing but collection of users

Creating users:
	.useradd/adduser: Adding new user (ex: useraddd shiva)
	 shiva:!!:20413:0:99999:7:::
	a)shiva: This is the username you created
	b)!!: password is locked or not set 
	C)20413: date when the password was last changed
	d)0:Minimum days between password changes
	e)99999: Maximum days before password expires
	f)7: Warining period before password ecpiry
	g)::: = inactivity or account expiry
	
Setting and managing passwords:
	.passwd: set or change user password (Ex: psswd shiva/kumar)
	
logging to account using username and password:
	.su username
	
To view all users:
	.cat /etc/shadow
	.cat /etc/passwd
	
Deleting Users:
	.userdel: delete user (Ex: userdel shiva/kumar)
	.deluser: Delete user and thier files (Ex: deluser shiva/kumar)
	
Viewing user information:
	.id: show users UID and group IDs (Ex: id shiva)

Group management:
-----------------
	.groupadd: Adding new group (ex: groupadd groupname)
	.cat /etc/group: checking group exit or not
	.usermod: Add user to a group (ex: usermod -aG groupname username)
	.groupdel: Delete group (ex: groupdel groupname)
